  "prompt": "Should organic peanut butter be refrigerated?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally recommended to refrigerate organic peanut butter after opening to extend its shelf life and maintain its flavor and texture. While some brands may not require refrigeration and can be stored in a cool, dark place, refrigeration can help prevent the natural oils from separating and minimize the risk of spoilage, especially if the peanut butter does not contain preservatives. Always check the label for specific storage instructions, as recommendations can vary by brand.",
